New Records: Angola set a new record by claiming two victories in the group stage, having never secured more than one win at previous editions.
Key Match Events: Gelson Dala scored twice for Angola in the 38th and 42nd minutes.
Mabululu scored for Angola in the 66th minute.
Neblu received a yellow card in the 17th minute.
Haukongo received a yellow card in the 14th minute and a red card in the 40th minute.
Iimbondi received a yellow card in the 63rd minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Angola's round of 16 clash with Namibia sees the Palancas Negras seek to match their best showing at the Africa Cup of Nations.
The Brave Warriors have already made history at AFCON 2023, making it to the knockout rounds for the first time in the nation's history.
Angola topped Group D against pre-tournament predictions.
Pedro Goncalves's men ended with seven points, playing a fourth game at the continental showpiece for the first time since hosting the finals in 2010.
Collin Benjamin's troops secured a historic victory over 2004 champions Tunisia in their tournament opener in Group E.
Deon Hotto's 88th-minute winner against Tunisia was Namibia's first-ever win at the finals.
